The entertainment industry has recorded not less than four deaths in April 2022. Comic actor Kunle Mak Tokunbo aka Dejo Tunfulu died on April 1, 2022 His colleague, Kunle Afod, announced his demise on Instagram. Afod wrote: “This is so sad, so painful, I can’t believe that you are no more.” The late actor was rumoured to have suffered unexpected bleeding during the shooting of his current film. One of Nigeria’s respected ex- referees Festus Okubule died on April 5, 2022. He was 80.   Take your mental health seriously, neuropsychiatrist urges…     ASUU insists on re-negotiated 2009 agreement, deployment of…     Tinubu, others to attend ‘Last Man Standing’ premiere April…   According to her daughter, Sola Taiwo, the former referee breathed his last around 5:50 pm on the fateful day. He officiated several domestic matches, as well international matches across the length and breadth of Africa. Popular Ibadan-based fuji musician Alhaji Isiaka Iyanda Sawaba aka Easy Sawaba died on April 6. He was 71. He was spotted in Lagos in March 2022 at the first colloquium of late Sikiru Ayinde Barrister at the Radisson Blu Hotel in Ikeja GRA. The veteran musician had a major career in the Fuji music industry in the 1970s and 1980s. Gospel singer Osinachi Nwachukwu died on April 8. Osinachi, who became famous for her hit song, ‘Ekwueme,’ passed away at 42. She was a lead singer at the Dunamis International Gospel Centre.